BBC - Pembrokeshire: Coastal Lives 3of4 Episode3 (2013)



Episode 3 of 4
DURATION: 30 MINUTES
Holidaymakers flock to Pembrokeshire's breathtaking coastal path over the summer. But what's it like to actually live there? This series follows the people who spend all their time by the west Wales coastline.

In this programme, local artist Lizzie Stonhold gets the whole of Fishguard knitting for her 'Granny Graffiti' project. Arch-rivals Solva and Newport take each other on in the biggest longboat race of the year, the Dinas Head challenge, and it's a testing time for blind walker Jack Lloyd as he tackles the coast path for the first time with his new guide dog Jackson.
